result.name: BEDU

reviews.text: Yummy yummy yummy! Simple menu to share every bite with friends. Seated at the bar table so I could look at how the kitchen works, I really enjoyed the food! Nice vibes too.

Spacious, unlike many in & around Central. A bit of walk from central MTR station. Food presentation, taste, service is very good. In general ~hkd200pp for lunch on weekends. Overall good place for meeting friends

Quaint restaurant in central serving Middle Eastern. Though menu has limited choices but the offering is sufficient to satisfy my appetite. Must have the lamb, fattoush, hummus. Seats are limited. Advisable to reserve

Nice Middle Eastern-focused restaurant. It has a fairly spacious dining area with a cosy feel to it thanks to the heavy emphasis on wood decor. Meals are fairly small and slightly pricy, but the quality and style of food provides a great value. Service can be a bit slow so don't go here in a rush. Also be mindful of the desserts being very sweet and very filling.
Great feed, strong flavours, nice interpretation of North African cuisine. Modern setup and good ambience too.
